01:52:02.960 --> 01:52:03.131
And I believe if you're here tonight and you feel that tug and you feel your butterflies and all the things you feel—"Oh goodness, do you think He would allow me to come home?

01:52:03.131 --> 01:52:03.474
"—yes.

01:52:03.474 --> 01:52:25.751
Just like the prodigal, he was laying in the pigpen and he said to himself—he came to himself and said, "If I could just go back to my father's house and be a servant.

01:52:25.751 --> 01:52:48.448
" But what he didn't know is the father was waiting with his arms wide open with the robe, and he said, "Kill the fatted calf, my son's home or my daughter's home in your case or whoever you are.

01:53:13.600 --> 01:53:13.840
" You say, "Oh, will He do the same for me?

01:53:13.840 --> 01:53:32.017
" He's no respecter of persons; what He'd do for one, He'll do for thousands and millions.

01:53:32.017 --> 01:53:48.709
So, I believe that tonight is your night of coming back home.

01:53:48.719 --> 01:54:14.994
But you've got to get radical and get all in because you're running out of time.

01:54:14.994 --> 01:54:41.419
Or you could be the person that's never asked Jesus and you said, "Do you think He would accept me into His kingdom?

01:54:41.419 --> 01:54:59.211
